Former Budalang&rsquo;i MP Raphael Wanjala has finally given in to pressure from some leaders and supporters and ditched the Jubilee Party for ODM.He has been a key supporter of the national government in Western.Wanjala on Thursday said he ditched Jubilee because Deputy President William Ruto ignored the role he played in marketing JP in Budalang&rsquo;i. &ldquo;Ruto instead opted to work with MP Ababu Namwamba, who is from a different political outfit,&rdquo; he said.Wanjala spoke to supporters, who included two MCA aspirants at Port Victoria trading centre. He said he had no option but to respect the will of the majority.He told ODM leaders to forgive him, saying he is scheduled to meet party leader Raila Odinga on Monday. Wanjala said he witnessed the problems his supporters went through under Jubilee.